  "summary": "Oversized OTLP HTTP response bodies can cause memory exhaustion in go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp",
  "details": "The OTLP HTTP exporters (traces, metrics, and logs) do not limit the size of the HTTP response body read from the collector. A malicious or misconfigured collector can send a large response body, leading to excessive memory consumption and potential process termination (OOM).",
